Title : Oakley Academy
Text : {{Orphan|date=October 2017}}

The '''Oakley Academy''' was a high school operated by [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] (LDS Church) located in [[Oakley, Idaho|Oakley]], [[Idaho]].<ref>Davis, Ellis Arthur: [https://books.google.com/books?id=ZyRPAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA95&lpg=PA95&dq=%22oakley+academy%22+idaho&source=bl&ots=-ZVbWcE78Q&sig=s8Mx-Ev3y1gW3e6rDYF227lI5VU&hl=en&sa=X&ei=W_JdU_emJKzyyAHCxIDoAw&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAjgK#v=snippet&q=%22oakley%20academy%22&f=false ''Davis' New Commercial Encyclopedia: Washington, Oregon and Idaho, The Pacific Northwest'']. 1909.</ref><ref>The Character Builder Leag: ''The Character Builder'', vol. 31 issues 3-12. 1918.</ref> It was founded in 1901. By 1906, it had 130 students and six teachers, and its building and grounds were valued at $12,000 dollars.<ref name="State">Idaho. Bureau of Immigration, Labor and Statistics: ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=HDoCAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA125&lpg=PA125&dq=oakley+academy+idaho&source=bl&ots=1t2ZdI7EPY&sig=PCfCVWddfcWoRa1zwDREx5jloW0&hl=en&sa=X&ei=j_BdU7nsL4LQyAGGoYCYDQ&ved=0CGcQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=oakley%20academy%20idaho&f=false The State of Idaho].'' 1906.</ref>

